Opdracht 1 - Wanneer gebruik je een int, long, double of float?
int 32-bit : This will have a minimum value of 0 and a maximum value of 232-1.
long 64-bit : The long data type can have values from -263 to 263-1 (64-bit signed two's complement integer).
float 32-bit :The float data type is a single-precision 32-bit floating-point. It should never be used for precise values such as currency.
double 64-bit : The double data type is a double-precision 64-bit floating-point.
                It should never be used for precise values such as currency.

